ce:section.ce:para:
The performance of the developed sensor for the determination of 6-MP (1000 mg L−1) was studied in the presence of NaCl, KCl, glucose, CaCl2, vitamin C, MgCl2, fructose, NaF, AlCl3, CuSO4, Lysine, and Glutathione in the same concentration of the analyte (Fig. 6
                           ) According to the obtained results, some interferents increased the fluorescent emission (such as NaF and NaCl) while the others quenched the fluorescent emission. Such effects from different cations or anions are consistent with previous reports in developing fluorescence sensors [26,27]. Intraday and interday analyses were used to evaluate the repeatability of the developed sensor. For the intraday experiment (Fig. 5
                           ), the sensor's response towards 60 mg L−1 6-MP was monitored during a day at different hours while the second experiment was performed on five different days. The relative standard deviations (RSD%) calculated for each were 0.44% and 0.48%, respectively.
